\paragraph{Meadow}

The meadow network in Figure \ref{fig:plotweb.meadow} presents 284 pollination interactions between all insect functional groups and 22 plant species mainly distributed within the families Lamiaceae, Asteraceae, Fabaceae, and Apiaceae. Some plant species attract multiple pollinator groups, like \textit{Cephalaria transsylvanica} (L.) Roem. \& Schult., \textit{Torilis arvensis} (Huds.) Link and\textit{Helminthotheca echioides} L.. Other species like \textit{Borago officinalis} L. or \textit{Phalaris aquatica} L. show specialized connections. Bees and beetles dominate the network, butterflies, hoverflies, and wasps are present with moderate interaction breadth. Moths show fewer connections. 

